reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super cute shoes!
reviews.reviewText: My daughter wore these for a recent event at school. She said they were comfortable and easy to put on. She was able to dance all evening and spent lots of time on her feet without any pain. They are true to size.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If you hate toe cleavage I feel bad for you son - I got 99 problems, but this shoe ain't one
reviews.reviewText: I was never crazy about her as a celebrity, but I continue to be a huge fan of the Jessica Simpson brand, especially the shoes. I fully intend to wear these until they're falling off, then order another pair.Fit: Perfect. I have normal-width feet that generally fit into a 9 or 9.5 in most shoes. I went with the 9.5 here, and it fits like a dream.Style: Couldn't be better. I purchased the taupe, which has maybe just slightly more grey than displayed, but it's still a warm and beautiful, year-round color. I especially like that the body of the shoe is a matte suede while the straps are a shiny satin. It's a nice texture variation and an extra nod to the design of a real ballet shoe.Pros:- insanely comfortable - those smooth satiny straps wrap securely around the ankle without choking or chafing- versatile - can't wait to wear these with basically everything in my wardrobe, to the office, out to dinner, sightseeing on vacation, everywhere- reasonably priced - well made and a total bargain for $39.99 in my opinionCons:- literally my only complaint is that even the lowest low-profile socks are a no-go (the sides of the shoe are just too shallow)Yes, you can see "toe cleavage." Exposure of toe cleavage is not always faux pas, and in fact many upscale designers favor it for its subtle sexuality. If you're that worried about people seeing the cracks of your toes, then by all means avoid this shoe, but you're really missing out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute and comfy for my teenager
reviews.reviewText: I have been searching for a product for my teenager that has a long narrow foot. Because of the straps these stay on her feet well. Cute and does what we need.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 2, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Tiny bit tight at toe, comfy, well made, cute
reviews.reviewText: I love these shoes! I ordered my usual size and it is a tiny bit tight on top of my big toe and at the side of my pinky toe, but I think that will break in after a few wearings. Otherwise this shoe is so comfortable! There is some nice padding on the inner sole, and the outer sole is a thicker rubber than many flats have which also helps. The leather is pliable and hugs my foot, even at the top of the heel where shoes like this will often dig in. The elastic criss-cross straps are very comfortable, look so cute, and even give my foot a little extra support.My husband loves them and says it looks like someone took stripper heels and made them into a comfortable shoe. I think they look classier than that, but I figured I’d toss in his opinion too. Haha.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 26, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful, nice quality flats for casual and dressy outfits.
reviews.reviewText: I really love these adorable truly ballet-style flats! They do run a little small, I am very squarely a size 7 shoe everywhere I go, but I had to return my size 7 in these and get the 7.5. The half-size up worked perfectly for me. I love these flats because they're really cute and they can be worn with a casual or dressy outfit. I wore these for my college graduation ceremonies and they were perfect! They are comfortable to wear all day, but I think they start feeling like they pinch your toes after a few hours, nothing unbearable, though.I don't like that they show a little bit of "toe-cleavage" but they're so beautiful otherwise it isn't worth deducting a star. A great feature that I didn't even think of that you get with this style is that the flats will hold on your feet even if they are dangling. Other flats would fall off your heels, but since these have the straps around the ankles, they stay securely on. The ankle straps are comfortable.They seem to be made of great quality material and at $20 they're a fantastic price for nice Jessica Simpson ballet flats. I originally saw a pair of Jessica Simpson flats just like this but with a square pointe toe at Dillards for $80! They haven't dropped in price in 2 years so I'm happy that I found these on Amazon. And I think the round toe is a lot cuter than the square/flat pointe style toe.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and comfortable
reviews.reviewText: Love these shoes. Jessica Simpson never disappoints when it comes to shoes. The gold was great for my holiday ensemble and just having a stroke, they’re easy to walk in and stay on my feet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Adorable but painful
reviews.reviewText: These shoes are so, so cute, and I wanted to love them, I really did. But depressingly, it only takes about fifteen minutes of wearing them to give me terrible blisters on the sides of my foot and in my heel. Normally this style of flat works super well for me, so I was surprised and disappointed. I thought maybe I just had to break them in, but every time I’ve worn them has had the same painful blisters after a very short time. If you have longer toes, pass on these unless you like your foot bleeding.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars About half size small and comfy sole
reviews.reviewText: I bought these for a work party. To go with a themed outfit. They are a bit smaller than the true size says. I’d say half a size. I normally wear a size 7 in dress shoes and flats. I went with a 7.5 after reading reviews and I’m glad I did. They were a bit tight in the toe area at first but using a trick I learned some years ago (put a ziplock down in the shoe, fill the ziplock with water, and freeze them overnight) I didn’t have to kill my feet to break them in. The ankle strap is not overly tight. So if you don’t have issues with swelling. They’re just right. If your feet do swell then go with a wider shoe. The sole of them is very comfortable and they are on the thinner side. If your like me, and have a wider toe base than your arch area. Then I’d recommend a wider size, and a half size up. I do think they’re a bit pricey for what they are, but they’re definitely worth it. Especially given finding a flat with a strap is almost impossible. I wore them for 8 hours my first day and my feet were fine afterwards. If you are on your feet a lot. And don’t normally wear dress shoes, or flats then these will be a change. But they were comfortable. I plan to test them out again in a few days. Just be aware there is not a lot of arch support in these, and they are a half size smaller than their size says. So if you want some wiggle room I’d go for a size up. If you want a snug fit then a half size.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on March 23, 2019
reviews.reviewText: I had ordered a UK size 5 which should be a US size 7. They sent me a US size 8 so they are half a size too big. However, because of the elastic round the ankle this isn’t a problem. So far I’ve only worn them around the house but they are so soft and comfortable I’m sure they will get a LOT of use. Very cute little shoes with toe cleavage on show, which I like. They also arrived a week before the estimated delivery date which was a nice surprise.
Elegant. High quality material. Fits slightly tighter than expected.
Love them, I’m a size 9 and they fit perfectly.
